<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-530-652  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 530 652.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>IEEE Transactions on Computers  June 1990 v39 n6 p752(10).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>On symmetric error correcting and all unidirectional errordetecting codes. (technical)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Kundu, Sandip; Reddy, Sudhakar M.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Error detecting/correcting codes protect data from errors.andP;  Thedesign of binary block codes capable of correcting up to tsymmetric errors and correcting all unidirectional errors isdiscussed, and a class of systematict-symmetric-error-correcting/all unidirectional-error-detectingcodes proposed.andP;  The codes become Berger codes when t = 0; when t= 1, they are shown to be of 'asymptotically optimal order'.andO;Methods for the construction of nonsystematic such codes for t = 2and t = 3 are also presented.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Error CheckingError-Correcting CodesCodesBinary-Coded Notation.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>